{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_35","type":"agent_message","text":"I’ve narrowed the first breakage down to Hadoop’s PB-backed record factory. The minimal likely fix is a small `reflection` block for the factory singleton plus the PB implementation classes that `Records.newRecord(...)` constructs for `Resource`, `ApplicationId`, `JobId`, `TaskId`, and `TaskAttemptId`; I’m confirming those class names in the jars before editing so I don’t over-register."}}
